<br>
I agree, we warriors need some changes, much like the changes that the knights at one time needed.  I find that if I'm in a group with another warrior in LDoN, the group is a lot weaker, as the second warrior brings /nothing/ to the table at all, and I'm usually the second warrior.  <br>
<br>
I'd love to see some warrior utility in the game myself, other than the very brief moments where /defensive or /evasive are needed, or a knight cannot be found there's little use for a warrior.  (Though I'm fortunate enough to have friends who enjoy having me along even though my class can't pull its weight.)<br>
<br>
<br>
/Shield was a good idea, and while at 58 it is a lot less useful than it was, when I got it through my 40s, it was a great ability.  It seems to be underused, and the range on it is a bit too small.  Casters seem to leave the range much too often when I try and keep them alive a little longer now.<br>
<br>
 <br>
I'd be pleased to see it end up where the choice between a warrior and a knight actually involved some tradeoffs on both sides for a group rather than the current situation.<br>
<br>
-Vilis<br>
